The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Breathing space for tax payers

 OUR BUREAU

 New Delhi, June 30: The government today extended the time limit for making investments under section 54EC to claim tax exemption on capital gains arising from the transfer of a long-term asset.

 In cases where the capital asset was transferred between September 29, 2005 and December 31, 2005, the deadline for investment has been extended to September 30.

 In cases where the capital asset was transferred between January 1, 2006 and June 30, 2006, the deadline for investment has been extended till December 31.

 Under Section 54EC of Income-tax Act, the tax waiver on capital gains arising from the transfer of a long-term capital asset is granted if the capital gains are invested in certain bonds within a period of six months after the date of such transfer. With effect from April 1, such gains can be invested only in the notified bonds of Rural Electrification Corporation Ltd and National Highways Authority of India, a press note said. 




